<tr id="L301"><td><a href="#L301">301</a></td><td>PARMEN:  Fellow academicians. Twenty five hundred years ago, a band of hearty vagabonds arrived on this barren, rough-hewn planet. There was a desperate hardship of backbreaking toil. And then a divine providence graced our genius and our dedication with the power of powers. And through it, our every need instantly materialised. We thereupon determined to form a utopian brotherhood. This night is indeed a festive occasion, for tonight, we welcome into that brotherhood its first new member.</td></tr>

<tr id="L302"><td><a href="#L302">302</a></td><td>KIRK:  Not yet, Parmen. You have to convince the doctor first.</td></tr>

<tr id="L303"><td><a href="#L303">303</a></td><td>MCCOY:  They'll never do it, Jim.</td></tr>

<tr id="L304"><td><a href="#L304">304</a></td><td>PARMEN:  Doctor, please. You have destroyed the festive mood of the ladies. We must recapture it at once. I know. What would be better than a serenade from the laughing spaceman?</td></tr>

<tr id="L305"><td><a href="#L305">305</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Spock, Uhura and Chapel are dragged over to a couch. Alexander plucks his lyre.</td></tr>

<tr id="L306"><td><a href="#L306">306</a></td><td>SPOCK:  (singing) Take care, young ladies, and value your wine. Be watchful of young men in their velvet prime.</td></tr>

<tr id="L307"><td><a href="#L307">307</a></td><td>SOMEONE: Deeply they'll swallow from your finest kegs. Then swiftly be gone leaving bitter dregs. Ah, bitter dregs.</td></tr>

<tr id="L308"><td><a href="#L308">308</a></td><td>SOMEONE: With smiling words and tender touch. Man offers little and asks for so much"</td></tr>

<tr id="L309"><td><a href="#L309">309</a></td><td>SOMEONE: He loves in the breathless excitement of night, then leaves with your treasure in cold morning light. Ah, in cold morning light"</td></tr>

<tr id="L310"><td><a href="#L310">310</a></td><td>PARMEN:  And now let the revels begin.</td></tr>

<tr id="L311"><td><a href="#L311">311</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: The four toys are paired up, and the furniture moves around. Chapel and Spock on one couch, Kirk and Uhura on the other. The men swap, then return.</td></tr>

<tr id="L312"><td><a href="#L312">312</a></td><td>DIONIYDE:  Oh, how faithless and fickle.</td></tr>

<tr id="L313"><td><a href="#L313">313</a></td><td>ERACLITUS:  Make up your minds.</td></tr>

<tr id="L314"><td><a href="#L314">314</a></td><td>CHAPEL:  I'm so ashamed. Please make them stop.</td></tr>

<tr id="L315"><td><a href="#L315">315</a></td><td>SPOCK:  We have tried.</td></tr>

<tr id="L316"><td><a href="#L316">316</a></td><td>CHAPEL:  Please, please make them stop.</td></tr>

<tr id="L317"><td><a href="#L317">317</a></td><td>SPOCK:  I haven't the power. I'm deeply sorry. We've failed you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L318"><td><a href="#L318">318</a></td><td>CHAPEL:  For so long I've wanted to be close to you. Now all I want to crawl away and die.</td></tr>

<tr id="L319"><td><a href="#L319">319</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Finally they are forced to kiss.</td></tr>

<tr id="L320"><td><a href="#L320">320</a></td><td>DIONIYDE:  Careful, Mister Spock. Too much love is dangerous.</td></tr>

<tr id="L321"><td><a href="#L321">321</a></td><td>ERACLITUS:  Remember, Cupid's arrow kills Vulcans. (general laughter)</td></tr>

<tr id="L322"><td><a href="#L322">322</a></td><td>UHURA:  (in Kirk's arms) I'm so frightened, Captain. I'm so very frightened.</td></tr>

<tr id="L323"><td><a href="#L323">323</a></td><td>KIRK:  That's the way they want you to feel. It makes them think that they're alive.</td></tr>

<tr id="L324"><td><a href="#L324">324</a></td><td>UHURA:  I know it, but I wish I could stop trembling.</td></tr>

<tr id="L325"><td><a href="#L325">325</a></td><td>KIRK:  Try not to think of them. Try.</td></tr>

<tr id="L326"><td><a href="#L326">326</a></td><td>UHURA:  I'm thinking. I'm thinking of all the times on the Enterprise when I was scared to death and I would see you so busy at your commands. And I would hear your voice from all the parts of the ship and my fears would fade. And now they are making me tremble. But I'm not afraid. I am not afraid.</td></tr>

<tr id="L327"><td><a href="#L327">327</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: As the camera closes in, Uhura's head is turned to obscure our view - and the lips don't quite touch.</td></tr>

<tr id="L328"><td><a href="#L328">328</a></td><td>PHILANA:  Parmen, let's get on with it.</td></tr>

<tr id="L329"><td><a href="#L329">329</a></td><td>PARMEN:  You are so impatient, my wife. Observe the doctor and learn. He's quite content to wait for the piece de resistance.</td></tr>

<tr id="L330"><td><a href="#L330">330</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: A table with a whip and other weapons slides across. Kirk and Spock approach it. Kirk takes the whip, Spock the red-hot poker. Just as they get to the women, Kirk turns.</td></tr>

<tr id="L331"><td><a href="#L331">331</a></td><td>KIRK:  You're half dead, all of you! You've been dead for centuries. We may disappear tomorrow, but at least we're living now, and you can't stand that, can you? You're half crazy because there's nothing inside. Nothing. And you have to torture us to convince yourselves you're superior.</td></tr>

<tr id="L332"><td><a href="#L332">332</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Kirk cracks the whip in front of Uhura's face. Alexander creeps away.</td></tr>

<tr id="L333"><td><a href="#L333">333</a></td><td>MCCOY:  Stop it, Parmen! Stop it! I'll do whatever you want me to do. I'll stay and serve you, but stop it!</td></tr>

<tr id="L334"><td><a href="#L334">334</a></td><td>PHILANA:  Parmen.</td></tr>

<tr id="L335"><td><a href="#L335">335</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Alexander is frozen in the act of trying to stab Parmen.</td></tr>

<tr id="L336"><td><a href="#L336">336</a></td><td>PARMEN:  Alexander again. He likes to play with knives. Very well, we shall indulge him.</td></tr>

<tr id="L337"><td><a href="#L337">337</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Alexander struggles not to stab himself, when suddenly he is released.</td></tr>

<tr id="L338"><td><a href="#L338">338</a></td><td>PARMEN:  Who did that?</td></tr>

<tr id="L339"><td><a href="#L339">339</a></td><td>KIRK:  (throwing down the whip.) I did.</td></tr>

<tr id="L340"><td><a href="#L340">340</a></td><td>ERACLITUS:  Impossible!</td></tr>

<tr id="L341"><td><a href="#L341">341</a></td><td>SPOCK:  Quite possible and logical.</td></tr>

<tr id="L342"><td><a href="#L342">342</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Spock throws away the poker.</td></tr>

<tr id="L343"><td><a href="#L343">343</a></td><td>DIONIYDE:  What is this?</td></tr>

<tr id="L344"><td><a href="#L344">344</a></td><td>PHILANA:  What's going on?</td></tr>

<tr id="L345"><td><a href="#L345">345</a></td><td>KIRK:  Platonians, listen to me. The next one of you that tries any trick will get hurt. Not only do we have your psychokinetic abilities, but at twice your power level.</td></tr>

<tr id="L346"><td><a href="#L346">346</a></td><td>PARMEN:  Not twice mine!</td></tr>

<tr id="L347"><td><a href="#L347">347</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Parmen controls Alexander and sends him to attack Kirk, but Kirk sends him back. To and fro he turns until finally the dagger is inches from Parmen's body.</td></tr>

<tr id="L348"><td><a href="#L348">348</a></td><td>PARMEN:  Captain, no! Captain! I beg of you, I'll do anything you say. I do not wish to die. Captain, do you hear me?</td></tr>

<tr id="L349"><td><a href="#L349">349</a></td><td>ALEXANDER:  Don't stop me. Let me finish him off.</td></tr>

<tr id="L350"><td><a href="#L350">350</a></td><td>KIRK:  Do you want to be like him?</td></tr>

<tr id="L351"><td><a href="#L351">351</a></td><td>ANNOTATION: Alexander puts down the knife by his own choice. Parmen is dragged out of his seat.</td></tr>

<tr id="L352"><td><a href="#L352">352</a></td><td>ALEXANDER:  Parmen, listen to me. I could have had your power, but I didn't want it. I could have had your place right now, but the sight of you and your Academicians sickens me. Despite your brains, you're the most contemptible things that ever lived in this universe.</td></tr>

<tr id="L353"><td><a href="#L353">353</a></td><td>PARMEN:  Captain, you knew that I intended to destroy both you and the Enterprise, yet you spared me.</td></tr>

<tr id="L354"><td><a href="#L354">354</a></td><td>KIRK:  To us, killing is murder, even for revenge. But there will be other starships.</td></tr>

<tr id="L355"><td><a href="#L355">355</a></td><td>PARMEN:  There's no need for concern. They'll be safe. Of late, I have begun to think that we've become bizarre and unproductive. We are existing merely to nourish our own power. It's time for some fresh air. We shall welcome your interstellar visits.</td></tr>

<tr id="L356"><td><a href="#L356">356</a></td><td>KIRK:  I don't believe you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L357"><td><a href="#L357">357</a></td><td>SPOCK:  That would be highly uncharacteristic. We must expect, Parmen, that the moment we leave here, your fear would be gone and you would again be as sadistic and as arrogant as your twenty five hundred years have made you.</td></tr>

<tr id="L358"><td><a href="#L358">358</a></td><td>KIRK:  Just remember, we can recreate that power in a matter of hours, so don't try anything.</td></tr>

<tr id="L359"><td><a href="#L359">359</a></td><td>PARMEN:  Understood, Captain. And you're right, none of us can be trusted. Uncontrolled, power will turn even saints into savages, and we can all be counted upon to live down to our lowest impulses.</td></tr>

<tr id="L360"><td><a href="#L360">360</a></td><td>KIRK:  You're very good at making speeches, Parmen. Just make sure that this one sinks in. Now move aside. Alexander. Kirk to Enterprise. Mister Scott, prepare to beam us up. I have a little surprise for you. I'm bringing a visitor aboard.</td></tr>

